!bc
file=$1
if [ -f $file ]; then
  cp $file $file.cop
fi
# This is Bash - what happens to this comment?
!ec

The same snippet typeset explicitly as Bash:

!bc shcod

file=$1
if [ -f $file ]; then
  cp $file $file.cop
fi
# This is Bash - what happens to this comment?
